Excel signature will be presenting an exhibition “Moods Relic of Courage,” a contemporary art exhibition by Jude Olotu. The exhibition which is scheduled to hold from 10th-18th April, 2022, will take place at Thought Pyramid Art Centre, Abuja. Olotu in recent years has exhibited internationally at the ‘World Art Dubai exhibition, Newyork and France showcasing his unique style of eclectic art. He has participated in group and individual exhibitions in Nigeria. His entrance into the international space was an explosion of accolades, from the international community and peers appreciating the work from a true grand master of the arts. His works stood out among the best in a plethora of exhibited art works on a world stage at the just concluded world art Dubai exhibition. It was a case of a bitter sweet experience as it was a marvel to behold the genius in his strokes however the non sale campaign left a taste of wants in the mouths of curators and art lovers alike. The genius of Olotu has created and nurtured many talents and students of the arts which has led to the creation of the Excel Signature Creative Hub in Abuja Nigeria. The creative hub is a place where creative artist are nurtured in fine arts, digital arts, metal art, wood art, sculpturing, product design,cinematography and production, music, and photography and given exposure to them on a national and international scale. This hub already paying dividends to society as an array of talents are being filled regularly due to the the mentorship and tutelage of the art maestro himself. Olotu hails from the Niger Delta Region of Nigeria. His love for art started as a child, growing up in the northern part of Nigeria, in the city of Jos where the landscape was as though it was painted on a canvas itself. 